https://www.codechef.com/problems/NUKES

Note : Well this is supercool because it teaches you counting. Show animations of how counting is done.
(We need to market this as a course)

a,n,k = map(int,input().split(' '))
    
li = [0]*k 
n+=1
for i in range(k):
        
    li[i] = a%n
    a  = int(a//n)
        
    if a < 1:
        break
    
print(*li)
        
        